Explanation:
1. Initialize a map (countMap) to store the prefixes and their counts.
2. Iterate through the word and for each character, check if the prefix already exists in the map. If it does, skip to the next character. Otherwise, add the prefix to the map and append the character to the prefix.
3. After iterating through all characters, sort the result vector and return the last element (representing the lexicographically largest string after all rounds)

Note: The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the word once. The space complexity is O(n) because we use a map to store prefixes and a vector to store the result strings.

